<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     ABSTRACT / WHAT IS SKINALYZE
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="about-section about-problem">
    <div class="about-section-inner reverse">
        <div class="about-section-img">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1579154204601-01588f351e67?w=640&q=80"
                 alt="Skin lesion under dermatoscope" />
        </div>
        <div class="about-section-text">
            <span class="section-tag tag-green">What is Skinalyze?</span>
            <h2>An End-to-End AI Dermatology Assistant</h2>
            <p>
                Skinalyze is an AI-powered web-based system designed to assist users in the early
                detection and understanding of skin lesions through automated image analysis,
                intelligent medical guidance, and explainable AI outputs.
            </p>
            <p>
                The system uses a deep-learning model trained on cloud-hosted dermatological image
                datasets, processed through a standardised preprocessing and augmentation pipeline,
                enabling robust classification even under real-world image variations such as
                different lighting, angles, and camera quality.
            </p>
            <ul class="about-list">
                <li>Automated skin lesion classification from uploaded images</li>
                <li>Grad-CAM heatmaps highlighting the AI's decision regions</li>
                <li>Domain specific chatbot for contextual medical follow-up</li>
                <li>Downloadable structured PDF diagnostic reports</li>
                <li>Severity ratings and actionable medical recommendations</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     THE PROBLEM
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="about-section about-how">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
        <div class="about-section-text">
            <span class="section-tag tag-pink">The Problem</span>
            <h2>Why Existing Solutions Fall Short</h2>
            <p>
                Skin lesion diagnosis today depends almost entirely on trained dermatologists,
                and they are in short supply, particularly in rural and underserved regions.
                Existing AI systems and dermatology applications face serious limitations that
                reduce clinical trust and limit their real-world usefulness.
            </p>
            <ul class="about-list">
                <li>Black-box decisions with no visual explanation of predictions</li>
                <li>No integrated medical recommendations, only classification scores</li>
                <li>No conversational engine for patient follow-up questions</li>
                <li>Mobile-only or research-only, not universally accessible</li>
                <li>No structured reporting for patients or clinicians</li>
                <li>Poor scalability when moving from research to real-world deployment</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="about-section-img">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1666214280557-f1b5022eb634?w=640&q=80"
                 alt="Doctor reviewing skin condition on screen" />
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     HOW IT WORKS
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="about-section about-how" style="background:#f7faf8;">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
        <div class="about-section-text">
            <span class="section-tag tag-green">How It Works</span>
            <h2>A Six-Stage AI Pipeline</h2>
            <p>
                Skinalyze processes your image through a multi-stage pipeline, from cloud-based
                data acquisition through to explainable results and medical chatbot support.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-section-img">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1576091160550-2173dba999ef?w=640&q=80"
                 alt="Medical professional using laptop for AI diagnosis" />
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="steps-grid">
        <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-icon" style="background:#eaf5ef; color:#0D5F4A;">01</div>
            <h3>Data Acquisition</h3>
            <p>Medical skin lesion datasets are stored in cloud storage. Your uploaded image is sent securely to the backend and forwarded to the ML inference API.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-icon" style="background:#f0ebff; color:#4B3FA0;">02</div>
            <h3>Preprocessing Pipeline</h3>
            <p>The image is resized, normalised, denoised, contrast-enhanced, and automatically augmented, ensuring robust inference even with real-world image variation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-icon" style="background:#fde8ef; color:#D6186A;">03</div>
            <h3>Detection &amp; Classification</h3>
            <p>CNN architecture; MobileNetV2 alongside CBAM classify the lesion type with a softmax confidence score.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-icon" style="background:#fce8ef; color:#850E35;">04</div>
            <h3>Grad-CAM Explainability</h3>
            <p>A heatmap is generated highlighting the exact regions of the image that influenced the model's prediction, making the AI decision visible and trustworthy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-icon" style="background:#eaf5ef; color:#0D5F4A;">05</div>
            <h3>Domain Specific Chatbot Support</h3>
            <p>A retrieval augmented generation chatbot queries a stored knowledge of medical documents plus internet sources to answer your skin-related follow-up questions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
            <div class="step-icon" style="background:#f0ebff; color:#4B3FA0;">06</div>
            <h3>Report Generation</h3>
            <p>The .NET backend compiles your results, prediction, confidence score, severity, heatmap, and patient details, into a downloadable structured PDF report.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

